body.description: ASUS TUF GAMING B650-PLUS WIFI is designed with military-grade components and game-ready features to provide unwavering gaming stability with the latest AMD Ryzen 7000 series processors and combines them with game-ready features and proven durability. Engineered with military-grade components, an upgraded power solution and a comprehensive cooling system, this motherboard offers rock-solid, stable performance for marathon gaming. Aesthetically, ASUS TUF GAMING B650-PLUS WIFI sports the new TUF Gaming logo, and incorporates simple geometric design elements to reflect the dependability and stability that defines the TUF Gaming series.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: ASUS is one of Fortune magazine’s World’s Most Admired Companies and is one of the top motherboard and gaming brands, as well as a top-three consumer notebook vendor. ASUS is driven by passion and innovation and dedicated to creating quality products for a future smart life, designing and manufacturing products that perfectly meet the needs of today's digital home, office and person. Our wide portfolio includes MG248Q, Chromebox and a range of devices and components, along with AR and VR. TUF GAMING B650-PLUS WIFI ASUS TUF GAMING B650-PLUS WIFI AMD Ryzen AM5 Micro-ATX motherboard, 14 power stages, PCIe 5.0 M.2 support, DDR5 memory, WiFi 6 and 2.5 Gb Ethernet, USB4 support and Aura Sync AMD AM5 socket: Ready for AMD Ryzen 7000 Series desktop processors Enhanced power solution: 12+2 teamed power stages, 8+4 ProCool sockets, alloy chokes and durable capacitors for stable power delivery Enhanced power solution: 12+2 teamed power stages, 8+4 ProCool sockets, alloy chokes and durable capacitors for stable power delivery Made for online Gaming: WiFi 6, Realtek 2.5 Gb Ethernet and TUF LANGuard Two-way AI Noise Cancelation: Reduces background noise from the microphone and audio output for crystal-clear communication in games or video conferences Comprehensive cooling: Enlarged VRM and PCH heatsinks, M.2 heatsinks, hybrid fan headers and Fan Xpert 2+ utility in Armoury Crate KSP-7: Aura Sync RGB effects: Stylish edge lighting design, addressable RGB headers and RGB strip header support.

Cooler By Design 1. Enlarged VRM Heatsink The extensive surface area of this heatsink covers the VRMs and chokes to improve heat dissipation. 2. Optimized M.2 Heatsink Design All M.2 slots have dedicated heatsinks, keeping M.2 SSDs at optimal operating temperatures to ensure consistent performance and reliability. DRAM Overclocking Performance DDR5 OC 6400 Comprehensive memory tuning options are the cornerstone of TUF GAMING motherboards. With TUF GAMING B650 motherboards, you can extract all of the potential out of your DDR5 modules, whether they're from an extreme-speed kit or an entry-level set that would otherwise be locked. PCIe 5.0 Support TUF GAMING B650 motherboards also feature one PCIe 5.0 M.2 slot to enjoy the fastest data transfers of up to 128 Gbps*, and all M.2 slots support for NVMe RAID configurations to take advantage of the latest available speeds. *Actual transmission speed will be lower than theoretical maximum speed.

Connectivity TUF-GAMING B650 motherboards reach new heights of performance potential with the latest version of PCI Express, while an arsenal of USB ports includes three Type-C connections, and Thunderbolt (USB4) expands compatibility and bandwidth even further. 1. USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 Type-C 2. PCIe 5.0 3. Front USB3.2 Gen 1 Type-C 4. USB4 Support Teamed Power Stages 12+2 power stages are each rated to handle 60 amperes, combining high-side and low-side MOSFETS and drivers into a single package to deliver power, efficiency and stable performance for all compatible AMD processors. ESD Guards ESD Guards prolong the life of components while preventing damage from electrostatic discharge, providing protection for up to +/- 10 kV of air discharge and +/- 6 kV of contact discharge — greatly surpassing the respective industry standards of +/- 6 kV and +/- 4 kV. Surface-mounted TVS diodes in a dual in-line package help protect your PC from voltage spikes.

WiFi 6 The WiFi 6 module is compatible with the 802.11ax standard and pushes theoretical peak bandwidth up to an incredible 1.2 Gbps. Perhaps more importantly for power users, it's optimized for more efficient operation on crowded networks with a lot of competing traffic. Pair your motherboard with ASUS WiFi 6 routers to fully experience the networking potential of WiFi 6. Realtek 7.1 Surround Sound The unique audio codec designed in close collaboration with Realtek for TUF GAMING B650 motherboards features an unprecedented 108 dB signal-to-noise ratio for the stereo line out and a 103dB SNR for the line in, providing pristine audio quality. M.2 Q-Latch The innovative Q-Latch makes it easy to install or remove an M.2 SSD without the need for specific tools. The design employs a simple locking mechanism to secure the M.2 SSD, neatly eliminating the need for screws.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works perfectly, feels very luxury and high quality
reviews.reviewText: I installed this motherboard to my am5 system recently. There isn’t a single thing wrong with it. It has some luxury features as shown on the ad. The most notable ones are probably 2.5g Ethernet, bios flashback, display port and HDMI, 3 pcie slots, and cooling plate for your ssd. It also came with a manual, sata cables, and screws.Overall, this motherboard was extremely easy and nice to work with as a first time builder. The places you’re supposed to put screws in (on top of the standoffs) have highlights on them, so it’s easy to see. The pcie tab is relatively easy to push down, the ram was easy to install (the channels are both gray). I had no problems with this motherboard and the manual came in handy many times. It doesn’t have a shield, nor does it need one, as it has one built in.This motherboard feels high quality and well made. My system is running perfectly with this in it. I love it, and I would recommend it to anyone looking to build with am5.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars a $200 great deal
reviews.reviewText: you are getting your money's worth in this board.. wifi reception is great. you get 3 NVME slots two pci that are spaced away from your two PCI e 5.0 slots. most of the board has heatsinks and stays very cool. set up was easy. and paper instructions make installation even easier. last board i bought gave me a QR code to scan then read from my phone. the over all sturdiness was great. there was just one issue was with bios updating.. you need to do v.1811 first then do v.2214. cap files need a fresh format on the USB stick in the Bios slot when updating.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Booted First Try, No Problems!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this Motherboard to go with a Ryzen 7800X3D, a 5700XT GPU, and some OLOy 5600MHz RAM, as that seems to be the highest speed that will work with this motherboard.The TUF Gaming B650-PLUS booted with no problems at all on the first try. The only hiccup was that it apparently needs a mouse and keyboard connected to show anything, even the EUFI. This was only a minor concern, as most motherboards are like this and anyone who has built a computer before will know.The CPU lever was extremely tense to pull down. If you've never used an AM4/AM5 socket before, be prepared for how hard you have to pull that lever. I had to Google check to make sure I wasn't about to break anything. There were plenty of screws, hookups, extra wires, brackets, everything I needed and MORE came with this Motherboard.I'm not entirely sure what was going on with the WiFi antenna... I tried plugging it in but couldn't seem to get Windows to recognize it or find any networks with it. I suspected I might have accidentally broken it when trying to put it together incorrectly, so I didn't dock any points for that, as it was probably my fault.Altogether, I wanted to write this review because I was a little bit worried reviewing something rated at 4-ish stars, but my experience was a BREEZE. Physical manuals were included (thank you, ASUS), and they must have improved their translating services because it's actually written in native English now. Great experience with this product!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Minor problems, but good overall
reviews.reviewText: I've only had this board for a couple months, so I can't vouch for its long term stability, but it has been fairly solid so far. I like that it supports ECC RAM (if you enable it in the EFI setup).Minor problems I've noticed:- The top-of-DIMM retaining clips on the black slots are physically different from the blue ones: the plastic caps that hold down the DIMMs are loose, and they rattle if there's any vibration on the board while they're empty.- It sometimes failed to boot, hanging at a black screen instead, during the first week or two that I had it. I don't know why, or why it stopped. (This was with BIOS 1616, and it stopped before new BIOS versions became available.)- I wish there was a POST error code display.- I wish PCIe 5.0 was routed to one of the card slots. I would gladly sacrifice bandwidth on one of the *three* m.2 connectors, or even give up one of those SSD connectors entirely, for this.- I wish the I/O panel had more USB ports.- I wish it had an optical audio output.- I wish the analog audio output had a bit more bass. Music doesn't sound as rich as it does with my Audigy PCIe card. Raising the bass in my amplifer helps somewhat.- I wish the bluetooth/wifi module was easy to examine and replace, instead of being buried under a plastic housing that doesn't seem designed for easy removal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy Install Works Great
reviews.reviewText: Install went well on upgrading old computer. I installed with Ryzen 5 5600X and 16 GB of ram. Updated BIOS to current version first, enabled TMP for Windows 11 Home install. All went great. I did have an issue when I was checked the BIOS on exit I opted to load optimized settings. That enabled Armory Crate which then caused issues for all the user accounts without admin rights. It tries to load Armory Crate on every logon and has to have admin rights. I called ASUS and had to have serial number for Motherboard. Sent me link for a Armory Removal App. I also had to disable the setting to load Armory Crate in the BIOS. That is what that Optimized settings enabled and once installed could not get rid of it till I used the uninstall app. Very happy with system runs great. Needed the Wi-Fi that is part of the motherboard and it works very good too. No Ethernet connection where computer is located.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Easy setup and first boot armory crate loaded up and had all the drivers updated. Super easy bios flash I'll probably use asus for my next build.

Coming from some other brand's horrid coil whine. (You will find which brand with searching B650+coil whine) Some say this is normal these days due to increased power consumption and variable driving voltage, etc etc. Nope, all lies! You should not hear coil whine when the system is idle!!And no, this board wasn't plagued by those 'bad' coils at all. As attached, it may not be perfect example, the OCCT stress fails to even instigate any coil noise from CPU side at all. And yes, my CPU is not a power hungry monster but the previous Gigabyte B650 was extremely noisy with coil whine.So, yes, if you're looking for a budget B650, definitely head into ASUS TUF although it is not exactly cheaper than any mATX boards. Yet, this board isn't more expensive than those 'high-end' gaming lineup.Here are some pros and cons.Pros:1. Now TUF is also providing the AIO PWM signal! TUF B560 didn't have it. But this newer generation seems to have the 4 pin slot for AIO.2. The CPU_OPT is still tied with the main CPU_FAN. Good for twin tower air cooling set up.3. Whopping 3 ARGB (5V 3pin) slots, still support 12V slots! It can be a budget, but we can still make it shine!4. XMP up to 6000 was no problem!5. VRM heatsink has stepping shape. I've installed a Thermalright Peerless Assassin (RGB variant) but it could hold even larger, i.e. Noctua DH-15, air cooler. But then again, I was able to put my hand into over the VRM heatsink to connect the CPU power cables!cons.1. It could be pros but half of USB 3.0 slots are C-type and they aren't all Thunderbolt. But these days, those PD charging cables are everywhere.2. The WiFi is not Intel, it is rather MediaTek MT7921 WiFi 6 (not E) I'm fine with not being 6E since 6E routers are expensive as heck anyway. But being MT7921 means Windows cannot automatically detect the WiFi card even after installation. You have to prepare a WiFi/Bluetooth driver separately. Also, considering what I've been through with Asus gaming laptops, it could cause some connectivity issue if you install older driver, didn't happen to me yet.3. Second PCI-E x16 slot becomes useless if you install 3 slot GPU, as seen in the picture. So, technically, the only expansion slot you can use, if you have a high-end gaming GPU, is the only tiny PCI x1 port. This is because the main PCI-E x16 slot is not located at the top slot.Yes, it is a bit budget side board with a few limitations. But it does its job fine. That other TUF I've mentioned was Intel B560 mATX and it is running fine under 24/7 running some simulation task since 2021 January. I should have went to TUF at the first.

Lleva funcionando desde el 1 de enero y hasta hoy día, 2 de septiembre no me ha dado problemas. La tengo funcionando con 2 m.2 de 1 Tb cada uno, marca DW_Black, un SSD Sata Kingston de 1 TB y dos HDDs de 500 Gb. Viene con tornillos para los m.2 por si se lo preguntaban. Además cuenta con dos disipadores y cada uno con su pad térmico correspondiente. Está funcionando con una RTX 3070, previamente con una RX 6650 XT; y un Ryzen 5 5600G. Debo agregar que no tuve que actualizar la BIOS ni nada de eso, pero si llegase a ser necesario cuenta con BIOS Flash. O sea, se puede actualizar via USB sin tener que andar colocando un CPU de generación pasada. Los únicos dos detalles son que, primero, vas a necesitar un fan hub si quieres conectar más de 3 ventiladores. Segundo. Puede que llegues a encontrarte con que los controladores del modulo WiFi/Bluetooth están desactualizados y Windows te dirá que ya tienes las últimas versiones. Me pasó cuando instalé por segunda vez el Win10. Pero por cualquier cosa que llegue a suceder, la solución es bien sencilla. Te vas a google y buscas "Controladores Asus TUF Gaming B550M-Plus" y en el primer resultado, en la página de Asus te descargas "Controlador Intel WiFi V22.80.1.1 para Windows 10/11 de 64 bits" e "Intel Bluetooth driver V22.80.0.4 para Windows 10/11 de 64 bits". En sí, la mother tiene un diseño decente. El RGB es jaja casi ni se nota. Siendo francos, hubiese preferido la ROG Strix B550m pero pues por desesperado terminé comprando esta, que cómo digo, no está mal, pero me gustaba más la ROG xD Pues nada jaja, eso es todo lo que tengo que añadir.

Es una motherboard de entrada. no es la mas barata ni la mas cara, funciona con cualquier procesador Ryzen fabricado hasta la fecha ya sea 1000 o 5000 eso es lo que me hizo comprarla.Tiene 2 espacios para NVMe pero una es 3.0 y la otra es 2.0 tengan en cuenta esto al comprar las NVMe y no gasten de mas (cualquier NVMe 3.0 es compatible en el puerto 2.0 pero estara limitada a 2000 MB/s mas que suficiente para guardar juegos).Tiene solo 3 pins ventiladores del case. mas 1 para el CPU y otro para el AIO pump para enfriamento liquido.Cuenta con 2 conectores RGB de 4 pin a 12V, NO son compatibles con ARGB de 5V.Tiene un boton de BIOS Flashback para que no tengan ningun problema para actualizar el bios en caso de requerirlo, es una maravilla por el precio.Los puestos PCIe son 3.0 pero si usas la segunda M.2 se desctivan todo excepto el primer puerto y el ultimo PCIe 2.0x4 y dos puertos sata de los 6 que tiene.Si compran tarjetas graficas de nueva generacion, funciona sin problemas pero tengan en cuenta que las RTX 3050 y la 6500XT usan PCIe 4.0x4 no usa los 16 lanes del conector y tendrian perdida de rendimiento, asi que si ese es la que piensa usar o compren otra tarjeta o otra grafica la RX 6600 y RTX 3060 en adelante si usan los 16 lanes y no tendran ningun problema de rendimiento con ellas.
